- POST /profile/2fa/enable
- POST /profile/2fa/disable
- GET /billing/summary
- GET /integrations/connected
- admin endpoints (/admin/roles, /admin/roles/:id, etc.)
- POST /audits/log-auth-event
- GET /audits/events

Security
- Password hashing: bcrypt (or Argon2)
- Tokens: JWT (RS256); rotate refresh tokens
- Secure cookies where applicable; HttpOnly, SameSiteLax/Strict
- CSRF protection for cookie-based sessions
- Rate limiting on login and token endpoints
- Brute-force protections and account lockouts with safe UX
- RBAC enforcement on all protected resources at server and guarded UI on frontend
- Validation: use DTOs and strict schemas; ensure Array.isArray() checks and default values

Validation Rules
- Data fetch results guarded with data ?? []
- All array operations guarded with (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- API responses shaped via const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining usage throughout
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

