    - GET /healthz / readiness checks

- Security & Validation
  - Passwords stored with bcrypt (or Argon2) + per-user salt
  - Email verification and password reset tokens are time-bound and single-use
  - JWT access tokens short-lived (e.g., 15 minutes) with rotation via refresh tokens
  - Secure HttpOnly cookies for tokens where appropriate; alternative safe storage with proper CSRF protection on SPAs
  - Implement CSRF protection for state-changing requests when using cookies
  - Role-based access control (RBAC) enforcement at API layer for resource access
  - Audit logging for all auth events: login, logout, token refresh, password reset, email verify, 2FA changes, admin actions
  - Rate limiting: per-IP and per-user, to protect login and sensitive endpoints
  - Brute-force protection with account lockouts or progressive delays
  - Input validation: strict schema validation on all inputs, with defaults to prevent undefined/null usage

- Validation & Safety Rules (Runtime)
  - Supabase-like results: use data ?? [] wherever a query returns potential null
  - Guard array operations: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - Initialize React state for arrays: useState<Type[]>([])
  - API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Optional chaining: use obj?.prop?.subprop when handling nested objects
  - Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
  - All API data shaping must defensively handle null/undefined values

- Integration & Flow
  - Frontend <-> Backend
    - Sign-up/login flows trigger token issuance; store access token in secure storage per platform considerations
    - On successful login, fetch user profile and RBAC roles; enforce client-side route guards and server-side checks
    - OAuth/SSO flows redirect back with authorization codes or tokens; server exchanges codes for user sessions
  - Profile & Security
    - Users can enable 2FA using TOTP (Google Authenticator/Authy) with QR codes
    - API keys management tied to user accounts with revocation and auditing
  - Audit & Observability
    - Each auth event creates an audit log entry with userId, action, resource, timestamp, and details
  - Data Privacy & Compliance
    - Sensitive data token rotation and secure storage
  - Accessibility
    - All forms and controls labeled properly; keyboard accessible

