  - Don’t expose raw tokens in UI
  - Show password strength meter; enforce password rules (min length, complexity)
  - Show 2FA status and setup flow clearly
- Accessibility & UX
  - Clear focus states, aria labels, and error messaging
  - Onboarding wizard supports back/next, progress indicators, validation on each step
- Error Handling
  - Graceful error messages with actionable next steps
  - Retry mechanisms for transient network errors
- Localization
  - Prepare for i18n if applicable (strings externalized)

### Backend
- Tech: Node.js/Express or NestJS (or equivalent) with TypeScript; or your preferred stack
- Security
  - Password hashing: bcrypt (or argon2) with proper salting
  - Token management: JWTs with RS256 keys; rotate refresh tokens; store in secure, HttpOnly cookies or secure storage
  - 2FA: TOTP with secret provisioning and recovery codes
  - Email verification and password reset tokens: secure random tokens with expiration
  - SSO/OAuth: implement OAuth2/OIDC flows for Google, GitHub, Microsoft; support enterprise SSO (SAML/OIDC)
  - RBAC: roles, permissions, and resource-level scoping
  - Audit logging: comprehensive events for auth actions and admin operations
  - Rate limiting: middleware-based throttling (per IP and per user)
  - Brute-force protection: exponential backoff, temporary account lockouts
  - Input validation: strict DTOs/schemas (e.g., using zod/joi/validator)
- Data Model
  - Create schemas per above (User, Session, RefreshToken, 2FA, PasswordResetToken, EmailVerificationToken, AuditLog, ApiKey, Role, Permission)
