  - Return validated shapes: ensure data ?? [] is used for array responses
  - Implement error handling with standardized error payloads
- Integrations
  - OAuth providers configured with client IDs/secrets
  - SSO endpoints and metadata retrieval
- Testing
  - Unit tests for token issuance/verification, password reset flows, 2FA, RBAC checks
  - Integration tests for login, signup, OAuth callbacks, email verification
  - Security tests: token theft, CSRF, rate limits, login attempt throttling
- Observability
  - Structured logging for auth events
  - Metrics: login attempts/sec, success rate, token refresh frequency
- Reliability
  - Idempotent operations for verification flows
  - Idempotent token creation and consumption
  - Idempotent user provisioning from SSO

### Integration

- Authorization Workflow
  - On app boot or session restoration, fetch current user and RBAC roles, then set global auth context
  - All protected API routes enforce RBAC by validating user roles/permissions
- Token Lifecycle
  - Access Token: short-lived; used for API authorization
  - Refresh Token: long-lived but stored securely; rotate on use
  - Attempt to renew tokens via /auth/refresh; on failure, redirect to login
- Email & Password Flows
  - Signup triggers email verification if required
  - Password reset triggers time-limited tokens and UI flows to reset
- OAuth/SSO Flows
  - OAuth callback handles code exchange, user provisioning, and session initialization
  - Enterprise SSO flow allows provisioning or linking accounts with existing users
- Auditing
  - All auth events create audit logs with details; expose a UI panel for admins to review
- RBAC
  - Admins can view/manage roles and permissions; end-user actions limited by assigned roles
- Data Integrity
  - Guard against null/undefined in all data flows; use default values; ensure array operations are guarded

## User Experience Flow

1) Entry
- User lands on UnifiedAuthEntry with options: Sign up, Sign in, Enterprise SSO, or Continue with Social (Google, GitHub, Microsoft)

2) Sign-Up Path
- User selects Sign Up
- Onboarding Wizard: Step 1 (Profile basics), Step 2 (Security & RBAC scope selection), Step 3 (Permissions & Modules), Step 4 (Onboarding tasks), Step 5 (Review & Create)
- User provides email, password (validated strength), accepts terms
- System stores user with emailVerified=false; sends verification email
- User verifies email via link; UI shows verification success or failure with guidance
- User is signed in (session created) and navigated to UserProfilePage or first-time onboarding dashboard

3) Sign-In Path
- User chooses email/password or Social OAuth/SSO
- If email/password:
  - Validate credentials; on success, issue access/refresh tokens; set secure cookies or store tokens safely
  - Load user profile, RBAC roles, and navigate to Home/Dashboard
- If social OAuth:
  - Redirect to provider; upon callback, link or create user; provision RBAC roles if needed
  - Sign in and redirect to profile/dashboard
- If Enterprise SSO:
  - Redirect to IdP; after successful assertion, provision user account or link with existing one; sign in

4) Password Reset
- User requests reset via Email field
- System sends time-limited link/token
- User clicks link, lands on PasswordResetPage; enters new password with strength checks
- Password updated; user logged in and redirected

5) Email Verification
- User receives verification email with token link
- User clicks link; system marks email as verified
- If verification fails (expired/used), show error state with retry guidance

6) Profile & Security
- User navigates to Profile: edit personal info, connect integrations
- Enable/disable 2FA; scan QR code to set up TOTP
- Manage API keys; create/revoke as needed
- View billing summary and manage module preferences
- Review active sessions; revoke any suspicious sessions

7) Admin & Auditing
- Admins access RBAC panels to adjust roles/permissions
- All auth-related actions appear in AuditLog with details
- Admins can review run artifacts and inter-agent traces if relevant

8) Error States
- Clear error messages with retry options
- Guidance for 2FA backup codes, account recovery, or contacting support

