- Ensure audit trails remain immutable and timestamped
- Ensure code is modular to support future module-specific RBAC requirements

Deliverables
- End-to-end TypeScript codebase (frontend + backend) shaped around the described APIs and models
- Detailed README with setup, configuration for OAuth providers, SSO, and migrations
- Migration scripts for initial data models (User, Roles, Tokens, AuditLog)
- Tests: unit/integration tests for auth flows, token rotation, RBAC enforcement, and password reset/email verify flows
- Documentation of security decisions and token lifecycles
- Example environment configuration for OAuth client IDs/secrets and SSO metadata

Implementation Notes / Guardrails
- Throughout all code, guard against null/undefined before calling array methods
  - Example: const items = data ?? []; const mapped = items.map(...)
  - Use Array.isArray checks where appropriate
- Initialize all array state with useState<Type[]>([]) in React components
- When consuming API responses, apply:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - const user = response?.data ?? {}
- Use optional chaining and destructuring defaults to avoid runtime errors

